Biography

2022 (Sophomore): Played and started in four games at cornerback, but missed the other seven games of the season due to injury...Recorded 15 tackles for the season and had one pass breakup...Had a season-high six tackles against Washburn (10/8/22).

2021 (Freshman): Played in all 11 games and made seven starts at cornerback...Recorded 22 tackles for the season, including two for loss, and two interceptions...Tied for the team lead in interceptions for the season...Produced a season-high five tackles against Emporia State (10/30/21)...Had interceptions in games against Nebraska-Kearney (10/2/21) and Pittsburg State (11/13/21)...Returned his interception against Pittsburg State 35 yards...Had one kickoff return for the season that went for 52 yards against Lincoln (9/18/21)...Ranked third on the team in pass breakups with five.

2020: Season canceled due to COVID-19 pandemic...Student-athletes retain year of eligibility.

Riverview HS: Named to Florida All-State Second Team in Class 8A as a senior in 2019...Selected to play in the Hillsborough County All-Star Game...Named to all-conference first team as a senior...Recorded 66 tackles and 8 interceptions as a senior, while also playing at wide receiver, quarterback, and kick returner on offense.
